Map the Sales Process to Acquiring a Customer

How much it will cost to bring a new customer to your product?

Common Pitfalls;
> Cost behind sales + marketing required to reach prospects
> Long, expensive sales cycles
> Costs associated with customers who do NOT buy
> Cycles within customers ( Corporate shakeups, business failure) etc


REMEMBER: Your Sales Process Changes Over Time
The three time period for sales

1. Short Term -- demand creation
    > Business focuses on creating demand
    > Business focuses on inbound marketing + sales

2. Medium Term
    > Business focuses on capturing larger clients + keeping costs low
    > Business focuses on retaining + fulfilling existing customer needs
3. Long Term -- 
    > Business focuses on fulfilling customer orders
    > Business focuses on management + success
How to Map your Sales Process


